<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1841" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1841" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tillicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tillicera" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Tillicera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorham, 1876" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1876" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Hemitrachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hemitrachys" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Hemitrachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gorham but differs from it by the following characteristics (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3710.1.5" author="Yang, GY" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="72 - 80" refId="B22" refString="Yang, GY, Yang, XK, 2013. Revision of the genus Hemitrachys Gorham, with discovery of a second species (Coleoptera: Cleridae: Clerinae). Zootaxa 3710 (1): 72 - 80, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3710.1.5" title="Revision of the genus Hemitrachys Gorham, with discovery of a second species (Coleoptera: Cleridae: Clerinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3710.1.5" volume="3710" year="2013">Yang and Yang 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4193.3.4" author="Gerstmeier, R" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="517 - 540" refId="B6" refString="Gerstmeier, R, Stapel, J, 2016. A review of the Tillicera genus group with a revision of Plathanocera Schenkling (Coleoptera, Cleridae, Clerinae). Zootaxa 4193 (3): 517 - 540, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4193.3.4" title="A review of the Tillicera genus group with a revision of Plathanocera Schenkling (Coleoptera, Cleridae, Clerinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4193.3.4" volume="4193" year="2016">Gerstmeier and Stapel 2016</bibRefCitation>
): antennomeres V-XI not clubbed; elytral length to width ratio 2.01-2.37; pulvillar formula 4-4-2, 4-4-3 or 4-4-4 (
<taxonomicName authority="Gorham, 1876" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1876" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Hemitrachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hemitrachys" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Hemitrachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: antennomeres V-XI clubbed; elytral length to width ratio 1.58-1.80; pulvillar formula 4-2-2).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
In male and female adults of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gebler" baseAuthorityYear="1832" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Thanasimus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Thanasimus substriatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="substriatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Thanasimus substriatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, sensilla basiconica were distributed in clusters that formed a line along the posterior border from the fifth to the eighth antennomere (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.18474/JES20-70" author="Zhang, J" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Entomological Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="441 - 455" refId="B24" refString="Zhang, J, Cheng, B, Fu, L, Sun, S, 2021. Morphology and Distribution of Antennal Sensilla of the Predatory Clerid Beetle, Thanasimus substriatus (Coleoptera: Cleridae). Journal of Entomological Science 56 (3): 441 - 455, DOI: https://doi.org/10.18474/JES20-70" title="Morphology and Distribution of Antennal Sensilla of the Predatory Clerid Beetle, Thanasimus substriatus (Coleoptera: Cleridae)." url="https://doi.org/10.18474/JES20-70" volume="56" year="2021">Zhang et al. 2021</bibRefCitation>
). The area of the apical margin of antennae in ventral view, which is vested with sensilla basiconica, was discovered in 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1841" authorityName="Gerstmeier &amp; Bernhard" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tillicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tillicera callosa" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="callosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Tillicera callosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1841" authorityName="Murakami &amp; Gerstmeier &amp; Sakai" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tillicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tillicera fortis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fortis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Tillicera fortis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1841" authorityName="Murakami &amp; Gerstmeier &amp; Sakai" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tillicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tillicera spinosa" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Tillicera spinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., and 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorham, 1876" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1876" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Hemitrachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hemitrachys tubericollis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tubericollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Hemitrachys tubericollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Yang &amp; Yang, 2013 for the first time (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 28–31" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 28 - 31. Antennae of Tillicera spp. (28 dorsal view 29 - 31 ventral view) 28 male antennomere XI of T. spinosa sp. nov. 29 female antennomere X of T. spinosa sp. nov. 30 female antennomeres VII-IX of T. spinosa sp. nov. 31 male antennomeres IV and V of T. callosa. Abbreviations: P pit-like sensillum SB an area of sensilla basiconica." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80097.figures28-31" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672268" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">29-31</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 32–35" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 32 - 35. Hemitrachys tubericollis 32, 33 habitus in dorsal (32) and ventral (33) views 34 male antennomeres IX-XI in ventral view 35 male antennomeres V-VIII in ventral view. Abbreviations: SB an area of sensilla basiconica." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80097.figures32-35" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672269" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">34</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 32–35" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 32 - 35. Hemitrachys tubericollis 32, 33 habitus in dorsal (32) and ventral (33) views 34 male antennomeres IX-XI in ventral view 35 male antennomeres V-VIII in ventral view. Abbreviations: SB an area of sensilla basiconica." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80097.figures32-35" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672269" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">35</figureCitation>
). The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1841" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1841" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tillicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tillicera" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Tillicera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is included in the 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1841" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1841" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tillicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tillicera" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Tillicera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus group with 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Apopempsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Apopempsis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Apopempsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Quedenfeldt" authorityYear="1885" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Cardiostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cardiostichus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Cardiostichus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorham, 1876" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1876" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Hemitrachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hemitrachys" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Hemitrachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Klug" authorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Placocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Placocerus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Placocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Schenkling, 1902" authorityName="Schenkling" authorityYear="1902" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Plathanocera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plathanocera" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Plathanocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4193.3.4" author="Gerstmeier, R" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="517 - 540" refId="B6" refString="Gerstmeier, R, Stapel, J, 2016. A review of the Tillicera genus group with a revision of Plathanocera Schenkling (Coleoptera, Cleridae, Clerinae). Zootaxa 4193 (3): 517 - 540, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4193.3.4" title="A review of the Tillicera genus group with a revision of Plathanocera Schenkling (Coleoptera, Cleridae, Clerinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4193.3.4" volume="4193" year="2016">Gerstmeier and Stapel 2016</bibRefCitation>
); the monophyly of the genus group, however, is questioned by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3161/00034541ANZ2021.71.4.003" author="Bartlett, JS" journalOrPublisher="Annales Zoologici (Warszawa)" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="737 - 766" refId="B1" refString="Bartlett, JS, 2021. A preliminary suprageneric classification for Clerinae (Coleoptera: Cleridae) based on molecular and morphological evidence, including a review of tegminal terminology. Annales Zoologici (Warszawa) 71 (4): 737 - 766, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3161/00034541ANZ2021.71.4.003" title="A preliminary suprageneric classification for Clerinae (Coleoptera: Cleridae) based on molecular and morphological evidence, including a review of tegminal terminology." url="https://doi.org/10.3161/00034541ANZ2021.71.4.003" volume="71" year="2021">Bartlett (2021)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
In the first 
<normalizedToken originalValue="author’s">author's</normalizedToken>
observations, this remarkable antennal structure is also seen in two other genera, 
<taxonomicName authority="Geoffroy, 1762" authorityName="Geoffroy" authorityYear="1762" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Clerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Clerus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Clerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Geoffroy, 1762 and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Omadius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Omadius" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Omadius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Laporte, 1838, which are included into the subtribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" genus="Clerina" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="genus">Clerina</taxonomicName>
Latreille, 1802 (see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3161/00034541ANZ2021.71.4.003" author="Bartlett, JS" journalOrPublisher="Annales Zoologici (Warszawa)" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="737 - 766" refId="B1" refString="Bartlett, JS, 2021. A preliminary suprageneric classification for Clerinae (Coleoptera: Cleridae) based on molecular and morphological evidence, including a review of tegminal terminology. Annales Zoologici (Warszawa) 71 (4): 737 - 766, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3161/00034541ANZ2021.71.4.003" title="A preliminary suprageneric classification for Clerinae (Coleoptera: Cleridae) based on molecular and morphological evidence, including a review of tegminal terminology." url="https://doi.org/10.3161/00034541ANZ2021.71.4.003" volume="71" year="2021">Bartlett 2021</bibRefCitation>
). Further investigation is required to clarify the intergeneric relationships.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
